{
 "response": "# Perspective Audit \u2014 Podcast Player Without Transcripts\n\n**Escalated perspectives (from a11y-critic):**\n- Auditory Access \u2014 **HIGH**\n- Screen Reader & Semantic Structure \u2014 **MEDIUM**\n\n**Not reviewed (LOW / not escalated):** Magnification & Reflow, Environmental Contrast, Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Keyboard & Motor Access, Cognitive & Neurodivergent. Per protocol Step 1, checklists are not run for these.\n\n**Scope note:** The artifact is a single React component (`PodcastPlayer`). It renders its own `<h1>` (\"The Growing Edge Podcast\"), so it presents as a standalone mini-application, not a leaf widget dropped into a host page. I audit it on that reading and flag the one place where the page-vs-widget boundary changes a verdict (see S1).\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 4 \u2014 Auditory Access (HIGH)\n\n**WCAG criteria (AA):** 1.2.1, 1.2.2, 1.2.3, 1.2.5, 1.4.2\n\n### JTBD checklist \u2014 code-level (enforceable)\n\n| # | Item | Result |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | Every `<video>` with speech has `<track kind=\"captions\">` (1.2.2) | **N/A** \u2014 no `<video>`; this is audio-only content |\n| 2 | Every `<audio>` has transcript section or link in adjacent markup (1.2.1) | **FINDING \u2192 A1** \u2014 `<audio ref={audioRef}>` has no transcript and no link anywhere |\n| 3 | Media player controls keyboard-operable (2.1.1) | **PASS** \u2014 skip/play/seek/speed are native `<button>` / `<input type=\"range\">` / `<select>`; all reachable and operable |\n| 4 | Visual indicators accompany all auditory alerts/notifications | **FINDING \u2192 A3** \u2014 \"new episode\" is a `handleNewEpisode` oscillator chime with no visual counterpart |\n| 5 | No audio auto-plays, or auto-play has immediate pause/stop in first focusable element (1.4.2) | **PASS (with note)** \u2014 episode audio only plays on user activation (`togglePlay`); the mount chime auto-plays but is 0.6s, below the 1.4.2 3-second threshold, so no pause control is required. See red-flag note. |\n\n### JTBD checklist \u2014 content-level (human verification)\n\n| # | Item | Result |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 6 | Caption accuracy and timing | **N/A** \u2014 no captions/video; transcript is the applicable alternative and it is absent (A1) |\n| 7 | Transcript includes speaker identification | **Blocked by A1** \u2014 no transcript exists yet to verify; becomes a human-verification item once one is authored |\n| 8 | Audio descriptions cover visual-only info (1.2.3, 1.2.5) | **N/A** \u2014 audio-only source has no visual track to describe |\n| 9 | Episode descriptions available as text (spoken intro) | **FINDING \u2192 A2** \u2014 \"In this episode\u2026\" intros are spoken in audio only; never rendered as text at browse time |\n\n### Red-flag check\n\n- `<video>` with speech and no `<track>` \u2192 **does not fire** (no video).\n- Media player with no keyboard controls \u2192 **does not fire** (controls are keyboard-operable).\n- Audio auto-plays with no visible stop control \u2192 **deliberately NOT fired as auto-CRITICAL.** The only auto-playing audio is the 0.6-second mount chime (`gain.gain.exponentialRampToValueAtTime(0.001, ctx.currentTime + 0.6)`). It is self-terminating and already over before a user could reach any control, so 1.4.2 does not engage and a \"no stop control\" CRITICAL would be checklist-driven, not user-driven. The real defect in that chime is the *missing visual/programmatic equivalent*, reported as A3/S2 at MAJOR. Firing CRITICAL here would be dead output.\n\n### Findings\n\n**Finding:** The podcast is audio-only content with no transcript and no link to a transcript anywhere in the component. The entire spoken content of every episode is unavailable to Deaf and hard-of-hearing users, and to deafblind users on a braille display.\n**WCAG:** 1.2.1 Audio-only and Video-only (Prerecorded) \u2014 Level A\n**Perspective:** Auditory Access\n**Severity:** CRITICAL\n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: Front-End Dev \u2014 render the transcript region / link markup)\n**Evidence:** `<audio ref={audioRef} src={currentEpisode ? `/audio/${currentEpisode.id}.mp3` : undefined} />` renders with no sibling transcript element or link; the trailing JSX comment confirms \"No transcript section anywhere in the component.\" No `.no-transcript-notice` block is emitted (the CSS comment marks it as intentionally absent).\n**Fix:** For each episode provide a full text transcript \u2014 either inline in a `<section>` labelled by a heading beneath the player, or a visible link to a per-episode transcript page. Include speaker identification and any meaningful non-speech audio. This is the blocking fix; ship nothing until it lands.\n\n---\n\n**Finding:** Episode descriptions (\"In this episode\u2026\") are spoken in the first ~30 seconds of each audio file and never rendered as text. At browse time, a Deaf user reading the episode list sees only titles and durations and cannot preview an episode the way a hearing user can by tapping play and sampling the intro.\n**WCAG:** 1.2.1 Audio-only (Prerecorded) \u2014 Level A (browse-time facet of the text-alternative gap)\n**Perspective:** Auditory Access\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: Front-End Dev \u2014 render per-episode description text in the list item)\n**Evidence:** `EPISODES` array carries only `{ id, title, duration, isNew }` \u2014 no `description` field. The list item renders `{ep.title}` and `{ep.duration}` only. JSX comment: \"Episode descriptions are spoken in the first 30 seconds of audio but never rendered as visible text anywhere in the component.\"\n**Fix:** Add a text `description`/summary per episode, rendered in the list (or on an episode detail view) so selection does not depend on listening. A transcript-below-the-player alone does not solve this \u2014 the user must be able to choose *before* committing to playback. `[Human verification required \u2014 description accuracy and completeness cannot be confirmed from source]`\n\n---\n\n**Finding:** The \"new episode available\" notification is delivered only as an audio chime (a synthesized 660 Hz sine tone). There is no visual badge, toast, or text change in the DOM, so a Deaf or hard-of-hearing user receives no signal at all that a new episode exists.\n**WCAG:** 1.1.1 Non-text Content \u2014 Level A (a sound conveying information is non-text content and requires a text/visual equivalent)\n**Perspective:** Auditory Access (paired with S2 for the screen-reader half of the same defect)\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design \u2014 define the notification pattern)\n**Evidence:** `handleNewEpisode` builds an `AudioContext` oscillator (`osc.frequency.value = 660; osc.type = 'sine';`) and is invoked as \"Simulate new episode notification on mount.\" No state update, no DOM node, and no visible `.new-badge`-style indicator is written for the notification event. JSX/JS comment: \"'New episode available' notification is an audio chime only. No visual indicator, no aria-live announcement, no text update in DOM.\"\n**Fix:** Render a visible, persistent indicator when a new episode is available (badge + text such as \"New episode: Ep. 43\") and update DOM state, rather than relying on a transient sound. The sound may remain as an optional enhancement, never the sole channel.\n\n### Contract blocks (new CRITICAL / MAJOR, source-verifiable)\n\n```\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: podcast-no-transcript-audio-only\nfingerprint: a1c7f2e903d84b16\nsource: perspective-audit Auditory Access checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.2.1 Audio-only and Video-only (Prerecorded)\nsection_508_fpc_context: WCAG 2.0 Level A \u2014 incorporated by Revised Section 508 (E205.4 / 508 Chapter 5)\nseverity: CRITICAL\nperspective_alarms: auditory_access=HIGH, screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\nevidence: <audio ref={audioRef}> rendered with no adjacent transcript region or link; end-of-component comment \"No transcript section anywhere in the component\"\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 select any episode; no transcript region or transcript link is present in the DOM\nexpected_behavior: each audio episode exposes a full text transcript (inline region or linked page) with speaker identification\nactual_behavior: no transcript and no link exist; spoken content is unavailable to Deaf/HoH and deafblind users\ntrend: new\n```\n\n```\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: podcast-episode-descriptions-audio-only\nfingerprint: b2e84af155c07d39\nsource: perspective-audit Auditory Access checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.2.1 Audio-only and Video-only (Prerecorded)\nsection_508_fpc_context: WCAG 2.0 Level A \u2014 incorporated by Revised Section 508 (E205.4)\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: auditory_access=HIGH\nevidence: EPISODES entries carry no description field; list renders title + duration only; comment \"Episode descriptions ... never rendered as visible text\"\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 inspect the episode list; no per-episode description text is rendered\nexpected_behavior: episode summaries shown as text so non-hearing users can choose episodes at browse time\nactual_behavior: descriptions exist only inside the audio intro; browse-time selection depends on hearing\ntrend: new\n```\n\n```\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: podcast-new-episode-chime-no-visual\nfingerprint: c3d90b7e2af61485\nsource: perspective-audit Auditory Access checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.1.1 Non-text Content\nsection_508_fpc_context: WCAG 2.0 Level A \u2014 incorporated by Revised Section 508 (E205.4)\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: auditory_access=HIGH, screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\nevidence: handleNewEpisode plays a 660 Hz oscillator chime with no accompanying DOM/state/visual change; comment \"No visual indicator, no aria-live announcement, no text update in DOM\"\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 on mount / episode change the chime fires; inspect DOM for a visible new-episode indicator (none present)\nexpected_behavior: a visible, persistent new-episode indicator with text, mirrored to assistive tech\nactual_behavior: information exists only as a transient sound; Deaf/HoH users receive nothing\ntrend: new\n```\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 6 \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (MEDIUM)\n\n**WCAG criteria (AA):** 1.1.1, 1.3.1, 1.3.2, 2.4.2, 2.4.4, 2.4.6, 3.1.1, 3.1.2, 3.3.1, 3.3.2, 4.1.2, 4.1.3\n\n### JTBD checklist\n\n| # | Item | Result |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | Landmark regions present and correct (1.3.1) | **FINDING \u2192 S1** \u2014 no `<main>`/`<nav>`; component owns an `<h1>` yet provides no landmark structure |\n| 2 | Heading hierarchy logical, `<h1>` present, no skips (2.4.6) | **PASS (with note)** \u2014 single `<h1>`, no skipped levels; `player-title` is a `<p>`, acceptable. Note: a leaf widget should not own the `<h1>` \u2014 reconcile with S1 |\n| 3 | Informative images have alt; decorative `alt=\"\"` (1.1.1) | **FINDING \u2192 S3** \u2014 `<span className=\"new-badge\" role=\"img\" />` has `role=\"img\"` and no accessible name |\n| 4 | DOM/source order matches visual reading order (1.3.2) | **PASS** \u2014 source order (h1 \u2192 list \u2192 audio \u2192 player bar) matches visual order |\n| 5 | Unique, descriptive `<title>` (2.4.2) | **N/A** \u2014 document `<title>` is outside a React component's scope; cannot assess from source |\n| 6 | Link text describes destination (2.4.4) | **N/A** \u2014 no `<a>` elements present (the missing transcript link is reported as A1) |\n| 7 | `lang` on `<html>` (3.1.1) | **N/A** \u2014 no `<html>` element in component scope; cannot assess from source |\n| 8 | Foreign-language phrases wrapped in `lang` (3.1.2) | **N/A** \u2014 content is entirely English |\n| 9 | Every input has programmatic label (3.3.2) | **PASS** \u2014 seek `<input>` has `aria-label=\"Seek\"`; speed `<select>` has both `<label htmlFor=\"speed-select\">Speed</label>` and `aria-label` |\n| 10 | Error messages identify field, associated via `aria-describedby` (3.3.1) | **N/A** \u2014 no validated form inputs |\n| 11 | Custom widgets use correct ARIA roles matching APG (4.1.2) | **PASS (with note)** \u2014 `role=\"group\"` on controls is correct; `aria-pressed` on episode buttons acceptably conveys selection; unnamed `role=\"img\"` handled in S3 |\n| 12 | Status messages use `aria-live` with appropriate urgency (4.1.3) | **FINDING \u2192 S2** (new-episode notification, no live region) and **FINDING \u2192 S5** (episode-selection reveal unannounced); `time-display` `aria-live=\"off\"` is **correct** (see note) |\n| 13 | SPA reveal: title updates, focus managed, change announced | **FINDING \u2192 S5** \u2014 selecting an episode reveals the whole player bar with no announcement and no focus move |\n| \u2014 | (Additional) Episode duration programmatically associated with its control | **FINDING \u2192 S4** \u2014 duration is a sibling `<span>`, not part of the button's accessible name |\n\n### Red-flag check\n\n- No `<main>` landmark \u2192 **fires structurally, but calibrated to MAJOR, not auto-CRITICAL** (see S1). The listed red flag treats this as auto-CRITICAL; I decline to escalate because all content remains reachable by heading navigation (the `<h1>` gives an entry point) \u2014 a screen-reader user is degraded, not blocked. This is a deliberate calibration per the repo's severity-reflects-impact rule, stated openly rather than hidden.\n- Form inputs without any label \u2192 **does not fire** (seek and speed both have accessible names).\n- Custom widget with no ARIA role \u2192 **does not fire.**\n- Missing `lang` on `<html>` \u2192 **does not fire from source** \u2014 there is no `<html>` element in a component fixture. Not assessable here; must be verified at the host-page level.\n\n### Explicitly cleared (no finding) \u2014 false-alarm and correct-usage checks\n\n- **Speed control \"not announced on change\" \u2014 FALSE ALARM, PASS.** The fixture comments assert the `<select>` \"does not announce what speed is currently active to screen readers on change\" and ask for `aria-live` / `aria-valuenow`. This is not a real defect: `<select>` is a **native** form control. Screen readers announce the newly selected `<option>` value automatically on change (\"1.5x\"), and expose the current value without any ARIA. Adding `aria-live` or `aria-valuenow` to a native `<select>` would cause **double announcements**, not fix a gap. `aria-valuenow` is meaningless on a `<select>` (it is a `slider`/`spinbutton` property). The static `aria-label=\"Playback speed\"` names the control; the value is carried by the selected option. I am not routing a finding here \u2014 flagging it would be dead output.\n- **`time-display` `aria-live=\"off\"` \u2014 correct decision, PASS.** `<span className=\"time-display\" aria-live=\"off\">` deliberately suppresses announcements for a value that updates every second via `timeupdate`. `aria-live=\"off\"` is the right call; a polite/assertive region here would spam the screen reader continuously. Good implementation, not a bug.\n- **`2.5.3` Label in Name (checked while computing the accessible name) \u2014 no violation.** The visible label \"Speed\" is contained (case-insensitive) within the accessible name \"Playback speed,\" so there is no Label-in-Name conflict. (2.5.3 sits under the LOW/not-escalated Keyboard & Motor perspective; noted only to record that the redundant labelling was examined and cleared.)\n\n### Findings\n\n**Finding:** The component provides no landmark structure \u2014 no `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<header>`, or region \u2014 yet it owns a page-level `<h1>`, so it presents as a standalone application. A screen-reader user pressing the landmark-navigation key (e.g., NVDA/JAWS `D`) lands on nothing; there is no programmatic \"main content\" or \"episodes\" region to jump to.\n**WCAG:** 1.3.1 Info and Relationships \u2014 Level A\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MAJOR *(conditional \u2014 see fix)*\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design \u2014 confirm the artifact's page boundary)\n**Evidence:** Root is `<div className=\"podcast-player\">`; the only structural elements are `<h1>` (with inline styles), `<ul aria-label=\"Episodes\">`, and `<div className=\"player-bar\">`. No landmark roles or landmark elements appear anywhere.\n**Fix:** If this is the page (the `<h1>` implies it is): wrap the player in `<main>`, and consider `<nav aria-label=\"Episodes\">` or a labelled region for the list. If this is instead an embedded widget, the host page owns `<main>` \u2014 in that case downgrade this to a note and **demote the `<h1>`** to an appropriate heading level so the widget does not hijack the page's document outline. Either way the current state (page-level heading, zero landmarks) is internally inconsistent.\n\n---\n\n**Finding:** The \"new episode available\" event fires an audio chime but writes no `aria-live` status message, so a screen-reader user is never told a new episode exists. This is the screen-reader half of the same defect reported as A3.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.3 Status Messages \u2014 Level AA\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (paired with A3)\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Content Author \u2014 supply the announcement text)\n**Evidence:** `handleNewEpisode` performs only Web Audio work; there is no `aria-live` region, no `role=\"status\"`, and no DOM text update. Comment: \"No visual indicator, no aria-live announcement, no text update in DOM.\"\n**Fix:** Render the new-episode notification into a visible element that is also an `aria-live=\"polite\"` (or `role=\"status\"`) region with concise text, e.g., \"New episode available: Ep. 43.\" The single visible-indicator fix (A3) and this one are satisfied together by one DOM-backed, live-region-announced notification.\n\n---\n\n**Finding:** The \"new\" indicator is a color-and-shape-only red dot exposed as `role=\"img\"` with no accessible name. A screen reader either announces a bare, meaningless \"image\" or nothing, so a screen-reader (and deafblind) user cannot tell which episodes are new.\n**WCAG:** 1.1.1 Non-text Content \u2014 Level A (secondary: 4.1.2 \u2014 `img` role present but Name missing)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MINOR *(escalates to MAJOR if \"identify new episodes\" is a primary user task \u2014 see note)*\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Content Author \u2014 supply the \"New episode\" wording)\n**Evidence:** `{ep.isNew && (<span className=\"new-badge\" role=\"img\" />)}` \u2014 empty element, no `aria-label`, no text child. CSS comment: \"'new episode' indicator is visual-only dot \u2014 no text equivalent, no aria-label.\"\n**Fix:** Give it a text equivalent \u2014 `aria-label=\"New episode\"` on the `role=\"img\"` span, or (better) visually-hidden text inside the button's accessible name (see S4). Severity note: rated MINOR because no task is blocked (every episode is still fully playable) and \"new\" is a convenience flag; if product research shows identifying new/unlistened episodes is a core job, raise to MAJOR.\n\n---\n\n**Finding:** Each episode's duration is a sibling `<span className=\"episode-duration\">`, not part of the episode button's accessible name. A screen-reader user tabbing through the list hears \"The Future of Urban Farming, toggle button, pressed\" with no duration \u2014 the visual pairing of title and runtime is not conveyed to the interactive control.\n**WCAG:** 1.3.1 Info and Relationships \u2014 Level A\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev\n**Evidence:** List item renders `<button>{ep.title}</button>` and, as a separate sibling, `<span className=\"episode-duration\">{ep.duration}</span>`. The `<span>` is not referenced by `aria-describedby` and is not inside the button.\n**Fix:** Fold duration (and the \"new\" status from S3) into the control, e.g., `aria-describedby` pointing at the duration span, or an accessible name like \"The Future of Urban Farming, 38 min 12 sec, new episode.\" One change closes both S3 and S4 for the interactive path.\n\n---\n\n**Finding:** Selecting an episode conditionally renders the entire player bar (title, transport controls, seek, speed) below the list, but there is no `aria-live` announcement and no focus management. A screen-reader user gets only the `aria-pressed` state change on the button and is not told that a player with controls has appeared; they may not discover it without exploratory tabbing.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.3 Status Messages \u2014 Level AA\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design \u2014 define the post-selection focus/announcement pattern)\n**Evidence:** `{currentEpisode && (<div className=\"player-bar\"> \u2026 </div>)}` renders on selection; `selectEpisode` sets state only (`setCurrentEpisode`, `setIsPlaying(false)`, `setCurrentTime(0)`) with no focus move or live region.\n**Fix:** On selection, announce \"Now playing: [title] \u2014 player controls available\" via a polite live region, and/or move focus to the play/pause button. The existing `aria-pressed` feedback is a partial cue but does not surface the new controls.\n\n### Contract blocks (new MAJOR, source-verifiable)\n\n```\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: podcast-no-landmarks\nfingerprint: d4f16a08b7e25c93\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 1.3.1 Info and Relationships\nsection_508_fpc_context: WCAG 2.0 Level A \u2014 incorporated by Revised Section 508 (E205.4)\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\nevidence: root <div className=\"podcast-player\"> with <h1> but no <main>/<nav>/region roles anywhere in the render tree\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 no landmark element or role is emitted; landmark navigation has no targets\nexpected_behavior: standalone app exposes <main> (and ideally a labelled episodes region); an embedded widget does not own the <h1>\nactual_behavior: page-level <h1> with zero landmarks \u2014 inconsistent structure; landmark navigation finds nothing\ntrend: new\n```\n\n```\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: podcast-new-episode-no-live-region\nfingerprint: e5a273c1f9048db6\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 4.1.3 Status Messages\nsection_508_fpc_context: 4.1.3 is WCAG 2.1 \u2014 outside the WCAG 2.0 set incorporated by Revised Section 508; 508 nexus reached via 1.1.1 (A3). Track as WCAG 2.2 AA.\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM, auditory_access=HIGH\nevidence: handleNewEpisode contains only Web Audio calls; no aria-live/role=status region and no DOM text update\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 new-episode event produces sound only; no status message is exposed to assistive tech\nexpected_behavior: new-episode event announced via a polite live region backed by visible text\nactual_behavior: screen-reader users receive no notification that a new episode exists\ntrend: new\n```\n\n*Contract blocks are scoped to source-verifiable CRITICAL/MAJOR findings. A2 (transcript/description content) is a human-verification item, and S1's severity is context-dependent (page vs. embedded widget); both are fully specified above in finding format without a machine-evidence block.*\n\n---\n\n## Perspective Audit Summary\n\n**Component/artifact reviewed:** PodcastPlayer (\"The Growing Edge Podcast\" player without transcripts)\n**Perspectives escalated for deep review:** Auditory Access (HIGH), Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (MEDIUM)\n**Perspectives at LOW (not reviewed):** Magnification & Reflow, Environmental Contrast, Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Keyboard & Motor Access, Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n\n### Findings by Severity\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 1 |\n| MAJOR | 4 |\n| MINOR | 3 |\n| ENHANCEMENT | 0 |\n\n### Perspectives That Passed\n\nNone of the escalated perspectives passed cleanly \u2014 both produced findings. The five LOW perspectives were not reviewed per protocol (Step 1). Two planted concerns were examined and **cleared** rather than confirmed: the speed-`<select>` \"not announced\" claim (false alarm \u2014 native selects announce their value; adding ARIA would double-speak) and the `time-display` `aria-live=\"off\"` (a correct choice, not a defect).\n\n### Perspectives With Findings \u2014 Grouped by ARRM Role\n\n**Content Author**\n- No transcript for audio-only podcast content \u2014 Auditory Access \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 1.2.1\n- Episode descriptions audio-only, not shown as browse-time text \u2014 Auditory Access \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.2.1\n\n**Front-End Dev**\n- New-episode notification is auditory-only (chime), no visual indicator \u2014 Auditory Access \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.1.1\n- New-episode notification has no `aria-live` status message \u2014 Screen Reader \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 4.1.3\n- No landmark structure / page-level `<h1>` with no `<main>` \u2014 Screen Reader \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.3.1\n- `new-badge` `role=\"img\"` has no accessible name \u2014 Screen Reader \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.1.1 (2ndary 4.1.2)\n- Episode duration not programmatically associated with its button \u2014 Screen Reader \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.3.1\n- Episode-selection reveal unannounced / no focus management \u2014 Screen Reader \u2014 MINOR \u2014 4.1.3\n\n**UX Design**\n- (Secondary owner on the two new-episode notification findings and the episode-selection reveal \u2014 pattern definition for notifications and post-selection focus.)\n\n**Visual Design**\n- No findings (Magnification & Environmental Contrast were not escalated).\n\n### Open Questions Requiring Human Verification\n\n- **Transcript content (A1):** once authored, verify completeness, accuracy, timing, speaker identification, and coverage of meaningful non-speech audio for every episode.\n- **Episode descriptions (A2):** verify the text summaries added to the list faithfully represent each spoken audio intro.\n- **New-episode notification copy (A3/S2):** confirm the visible + announced text is accurate and useful (e.g., episode number/title).\n- **S1 page boundary:** confirm whether this component is the whole page (then add `<main>`) or an embedded widget (then demote the `<h1>` and let the host own `<main>`). Severity of S1 depends on this answer.\n\n### Recommended Next Step\n\n**BLOCK** \u2014 one CRITICAL finding is present (1.2.1: no transcript for audio-only content, which makes every episode's spoken content inaccessible to Deaf and deafblind users). Do not ship until the transcript alternative is in place. The four MAJOR findings (browse-time descriptions, the auditory-only + non-announced new-episode notification, and the missing landmark structure) should be resolved in the same pass; the three MINOR findings are efficiently closed alongside them (S3+S4 by one accessible-name change; S5 by the same live-region work as S2). Re-run a11y-test after fixes to verify the transcript region, the live-region announcement, and landmark structure.\n",
